<br /><br />
<b><font class="print-title">Mana cap found, being removed</font></b><br /><br />
<font class="print-sub">Articles / EverQuest News<br />
<b>Date:</b> Aug 12, 2002 - 10:00 AM</font>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font class="print-normal">It turns out that there has always been a mana cap that we were unaware of, and it was set at 4250... meaning, with int/wis items and +mana items it has always been impossible to obtain more than 4250 mana, however with certain buffs it's possible to exceed this limit, but that's besides the point. It turns out that this cap is soon to be removed, which for those who have that much mana for it to matter, this is a good thing. You can find the discussion about it amongst your fellow Luclin folks <a href="http://pub106.ezboard.com/fluclin71335general.showMessage?topicID=7965.topic">here</a>.<br /><br />
<br />
</font>
</td></tr>
